The invention relates to a piece of sports equipment, particularly for grass skiing, comprising a frame (20) which
extends in a longitudinal direction and on which at least two wheels (1;
1a, 1b) that are provided with elastically deformable tires (3)
are rigidly mounted, and bindings (21) for fastening the piece of sports equipment to a shoe (22) of a person using said piece of sports
equipment. A front wheel (1a) is disposed in front of the bindings (21) while a rear wheel (1b) is arranged behind the bindings (21).
The riding behavior can be made to largely match that of alpine skis by the fact that an extension (25) which comprises a supporting
section (26) at the distal end thereof is provided behind the rear wheel (1b) on the frame (20). The supporting section (26) can be
